{"parse":{"title":"thanks","pageid":33788,"redirects":[],"wikitext":"==English==\n\n===Alternative forms===\n* {{alt|en|t'anks|thanx|thx|tnx|10x|fanks||all|_|nonstandard}}\n\n===Etymology===\n{{ety|en|:inh|enm:thanks<ety:inh<ang:þanc<alt:þancas>>>}}\nFrom {{inh|en|enm|thanks}}, {{m|enm|thankes}}, from {{inh|en|ang|þancas|t=thanks}}, from {{inh|en|gem-pro|*þankōs}}, nominative plural of {{m|gem-pro|*þankaz||thought, gratitude}}, from {{der|en|ine-pro|*teng-||to think, feel}}. More at {{l|en|thank}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{a|en|non-æ-raising}}\n** {{IPA|en|/ˈθæŋks/|[ˈθæŋks]}}\n*** {{a|en|th-fronting}}\n**** {{IPA|en|/ˈfæŋks/|[ˈfæŋks]|a=UK}}\n** {{IPA|en|/ˈðæŋks/|[ˈðæŋks]}}\n* {{a|en|æ-raising}}\n** {{a|en|US|CA}}\n*** {{IPA|en|/ˈθeɪ̯ŋks/|[ˈθeɪ̯ŋks]|~|/ˈθɛ̃ŋks/|[ˈθɛ̃ŋks]}}\n**** {{audio|en|en-us-thanks.ogg|a=US}}\n*** {{IPA|en|/ˈðeɪ̯ŋks/|[ˈðeɪ̯ŋks]|~|/ˈðɛ̃ŋks/|[ˈðɛ̃ŋks]}}\n* {{rhymes|en|æŋks|s=1}}\n* {{hyph|en|thanks}}\n\n===Interjection===\n{{en-intj}}\n\n# {{non-gloss|Used to express [[appreciation]] or [[gratitude]].}}\n#: {{syn|en|Thesaurus:thank you}}\n#: {{ux|en|Could you give me a hand, please?'' — Yes, sure. — '''''Thanks'''. —Have you got enough now? —Yes, '''thanks'''.}}\n#: {{ux|en|Would you like some potatoes? — '''Thanks'''. —How many?}}\n#* {{RQ:Shakespeare Midsummer|5|1|passage='''Thanks,''' courteous wall: Jove shield thee well for this!}}\n\n====Derived terms====\n{{col|en|thankies|thanksgive|thanksgiver|thanksgiving|thanksies|thanks a lot|many thanks|no thanks|no thanks to|thanks a bunch|thanks a heap|thanks a million|thanks a ton|thanks be|thanks for coming|thanks in advance|vote of thanks|thanks, but no thanks|thanks for asking|thanks for nothing|thanks for your help|thanks for coming to my TED Talk}}\n\n====Translations====\n{{trans-top|used to express appreciation or gratitude}}\n* Afrikaans: {{t+|af|dankie}}\n* Albanian: {{t+|sq|faleminderit}}, {{t+|sq|rrofsh}}\n* Ambonese Malay: {{t|abs|dangke}}\n* American Sign Language: {{t|ase|OpenB@Chin-PalmBack OpenB@FromChin-PalmUp}}\n* Amharic: {{t|am|አመሰግናለሁ}}\n* Arabic: {{t|ar|شُكْرًا}}\n*: Egyptian Arabic: {{t|arz|شكرا|tr=šukran}}, {{t|arz|مرسي|tr=mersī}}\n*: Hijazi Arabic: {{t|acw|شُكْرًا|tr=šukran}}, {{t|acw|تِسْلَم|tr=tislam}}\n*: Moroccan Arabic: {{t|ary|شكرا|tr=šukran}}\n* Aramaic:\n*: Assyrian Neo-Aramaic: {{t|aii|ܨܦܵܝ|tr=ṣpāy}}\n* Armenian: {{t+|hy|շնորհակալություն}}\n* Assamese: {{t|as|ধন্যবাদ}}, {{t|as|থেংকিউ}}\n* Asturian: {{t+|ast|gracies}}\n* Azerbaijani: {{t|az|çox sağ ol}}, {{t|az|təşəkkür edirəm}}\n* Bangi: {{t|bni|litondi}}\n* Basque: {{t+|eu|eskerrik asko}}, {{t+|eu|mila esker}}, {{t|eu|esker aunitz}}\n* Belarusian: {{t|be|дзя́кую}}, {{t|be|дзя́куй}}, {{t|be|спасі́ба}}\n* Bengali: {{t+|bn|ধন্যবাদ}}, {{t+|bn|শুকরিয়া}}\n* Breton: {{t+|br|trugarez}}\n* Bulgarian: {{t+|bg|благодаря́}}, {{t+|bg|мерси́}}\n* Burmese: {{t|my|ကျေးဇူးတင်ပါသည်}}\n* Catalan: {{t+|ca|gràcies}}, {{t+|ca|mercès}}\n* Chamicuro: {{t|ccc|osolopaki}}\n* Cherokee: {{t|chr|ᎠᎾᎵᎮᎵᎬ}}, {{t+|chr|ᏩᏙ}}\n* Chinese:\n*: Cantonese: {{t+|yue|多謝|tr=do1 ze6}} {{qualifier|for something received}}, {{t+|yue|唔該|tr=m4 goi1}} {{qualifier|for something performed}}\n*: Dungan: {{t|dng|рахмат}}, {{t|dng|дуәще}}\n*: Hokkien: {{t+|nan-hbl|多謝|tr=to-siā / to-siǎ / to͘-siā}}\n*: Mandarin: {{t+|cmn|謝謝|tr=xièxie}}, {{t+|cmn|多謝|tr=duōxiè}}, {{qualifier|slang}} {{t+|cmn|三Q|tr=sānkiù}}\n* Chinook Jargon: {{t|chn|masi}}\n* Chukchi: {{t|ckt|рэӄуԓымӈэ|tr=rėquḷymṇė}}, {{t|ckt|вэԓынкыӄун|tr=vėḷynkyqun}}\n* Cia-Cia: {{t|cia|tarima kasi}}, {{t|cia|따리마 까시}}\n* Cornish: {{t|kw|meur ras}}\n* Czech: {{t+|cs|díky}}\n* Danish: {{t+|da|tak}}\n* Dutch: {{t+|nl|bedankt}}, {{t+|nl|dank je}}, {{t+|nl|dank u}}, {{t+|nl|thanks}} {{qualifier|informal}}, {{t+|nl|merci}} {{qualifier|Belgium, informal}}\n* Esperanto: {{t+|eo|dankon}}\n* Estonian: {{t|et|tänan}}, {{t+|et|aitäh}}\n* Ewe: {{t|ee|akpe}}\n* Faroese: {{t|fo|takk}}\n* Finnish: {{t+|fi|kiitos}}, {{t+|fi|kiitti}}\n* French: {{t+|fr|merci}}\n* Frisian:\n*: West Frisian: {{t|fy|tankewol}}, {{t|fy|tanke}}\n* Galician: {{t|gl|grazas}}, {{qualifier|informal}} {{t|gl|graciñas}}\n* Garo: {{t|grt|mitela}}\n* Georgian: {{t|ka|გმადლობთ}}, {{t|ka|მადლობა}}, {{t|ka|გმადლობ}}\n* German: {{t+|de|danke}}\n* Greek: {{t+|el|ευχαριστώ}}\n*: Ancient Greek: {{t|grc|εὐχαριστῶ}}\n* Hebrew: {{t+|he|תּוֹדָה|tr=todá}}, {{t+|he|חֵן חֵן|tr=khén khén}}\n* Hindi: {{t+|hi|धन्यवाद}}, {{t+|hi|शुक्रिया}}, {{t|hi|थैंक्स}}, {{t|hi|थैंक्यू}}\n* Hungarian: {{t+|hu|köszönöm}}, {{t+|hu|köszi}} {{qualifier|informal}}\n* Icelandic: {{t+|is|takk}} {{qualifier|informal}}, {{t+|is|takk fyrir}} {{qualifier|formal}}, {{t|is|þakka þér}}\n* Ido: {{t+|io|danko}}\n* Igbo: {{t|ig|ị́mẹ̄lá}}\n* Indonesian: {{t+|id|terima kasih}}\n* Irish: {{qualifier|to one person}} {{t|ga|go raibh maith agat}}, {{qualifier|to more than one person}} {{t|ga|go raibh maith agaibh}}\n* Italian: {{t+|it|grazie}}\n* Japanese: {{t+|ja|ありがとう|tr=arigatō}}, {{t+|ja|どうも|tr=dōmo}}, {{t+|ja|ありがとうございます|tr=arigatō gozaimasu}}\n* Jingpho: {{t|kac|chyeju kaba sai}}\n* Kazakh: {{t|kk|сізге рахмет}}, {{t|kk|рақмет сізге}}\n* Khmer: {{t|km|អរគុណ}}\n* Korean: {{t|ko|고마워}}, {{t+|ko|고맙다}}, {{t|ko|고마워요}}, {{t|ko|고맙습니다}}\n* Kurdish:\n*: Central Kurdish: {{t+|ckb|سوپاس}}, {{t|ckb|سپاس}}\n*: Northern Kurdish: {{t+|kmr|spas}}, {{t+|kmr|memnûn}}, {{t+|kmr|teşekur}}\n* Kyrgyz: {{t+|ky|рахмат}}, {{t+|ky|ыракмат}}\n* Ladino: {{t|lad|grasias}}, {{t|lad|mersi}}, {{t|lad|shukur}}\n* Lao: {{t|lo|ຂໍຂອບໃຈ}}, {{t|lo|ຂອບໃຈ}}\n* Latin: {{t+|la|gratias}}, {{t|la|gratias ago}}\n* Latvian: {{t+|lv|paldies}}\n* Lingala: {{t|ln|litondi}}\n* Lithuanian: {{t+|lt|ačiū}}, {{t+|lt|dėkui}}\n* Luganda: {{t|lg|webale}}\n* Luxembourgish: {{t+|lb|merci}}\n* Macedonian: {{t|mk|фала}}, {{t|mk|благодарам}}\n* Malay: {{t+|ms|terima kasih}}\n* Maltese: {{t+|mt|grazzi}}\n* Marwari: {{t|mwr|धनवाद}}, {{t|mwr|धिनवाद}}\n* Mongolian:\n*: Cyrillic: {{t|mn|баярлалаа}}\n* Naga:\n*: Khiamniungan Naga: {{t|kix|thēumēi}}\n* Nahuatl: {{t+|nah|tlazohcāmati}}\n* Navajo: {{t|nv|ahéheeʼ}}\n* Nepali: {{t|ne|धन्यवाद}}\n* Nheengatu: {{t|yrl|kwekatú}}\n* Norwegian: {{t+|no|takk}}\n* Occitan: {{t+|oc|mercé}}, {{t+|oc|mercés}}\n* Old English: {{t|ang|þancas ic dō}}, {{t|ang|þancas ic secge}}\n* Palauan: {{t|pau|sulang}}\n* Papiamentu: {{t|pap|danki}}\n* Pashto: {{t|ps|مننه|tr=manëna}}\n* Persian: {{t+|fa|ممنون|tr=mamnun}}, {{t+|fa|سپاس|tr=sepâs}}, {{t+|fa|مرسی|tr=mersi}}, {{t+|fa|تشکر|tr=tašakkor}}\n* Polish: {{t+|pl|dziękuję}}, {{t+|pl|dzięki}}\n* Portuguese: {{t+|pt|obrigado|m}}, {{t+|pt|obrigada|f}}, {{t|pt|valeu}} {{qualifier|informal|Brazil}}\n* Romanian: {{t+|ro|mulțumesc}}, {{t+|ro|mersi}}\n* Romansh: {{t|rm|grazia fich}}\n* Russian: {{t+|ru|спаси́бо}}, {{t+|ru|благодарю́}}\n* Sami:\n*: Inari Sami: {{t|smn|takkâ}}\n*: Northern Sami: {{t|se|giitu}}\n*: Skolt Sami: {{t|sms|späʹsseb}}\n* Samoan: {{t|sm|fa'afetai}}\n* Sanskrit: {{t|sa|धन्यवादा|m-p|alt=धन्यवादान}}, {{t|sa|अनुगृहीतोऽस्मि}}\n* Scots: {{t|sco|thank}}\n* Scottish Gaelic: {{t|gd|taing}}\n* Serbo-Croatian:\n*: Cyrillic: {{t|sh|хва́ла}}\n*: Latin: {{t+|sh|hvála}}\n* Sinhalese: {{t|si|ඉස්තුති}}, {{t|si|ස්තුති}}\n* Slovak: {{t|sk|vďaka}}, {{t+|sk|ďakujem}}\n* Slovene: {{t+|sl|hvála}}\n* Sorbian:\n*: Lower Sorbian: {{t|dsb|źěkujom se}}\n* Spanish: {{t+|es|gracias}}\n* Sranan Tongo: {{t|srn|danki}}, {{t|srn|tangi}}\n* Swahili: {{t+|sw|asante}}, {{t|sw|nashukuru}}\n* Swedish: {{t+|sv|tack}}, {{t+|sv|tackar}}\n* Sylheti: {{t|syl|ꠡꠥꠇ꠆ꠞꠤꠀ}}, {{t|syl|ꠗꠂꠘ꠆ꠘꠛꠣꠖ}}\n* Tagalog: {{t+|tl|salamat}}\n* Tajik: {{t+|tg|ташаккур}}, {{t|tg|раҳмат}}\n* Tamil: {{t+|ta|நன்றி}}\n* Tatar: {{t+|tt|рәхмәт}}\n* Telugu: {{t+|te|ధన్యవాదాలు}}\n* Thai: {{t+|th|ขอบคุณ}}\n* Tigrinya: {{t|ti|የመስግነካ}}\n* Tlingit: {{t|tli|gunalchéesh}}\n* Turkish: {{t+|tr|sağ ol}}, {{t+|tr|teşekkürler}}, {{t+|tr|teşekkür ederim}}\n*: Ottoman Turkish: {{t|ota|مرسی|tr=mersi|id=thanks}}\n* Turkmen: {{t|tk|sagboluň}}, {{t|tk|spasiba}}\n* Ukrainian: {{t+|uk|дя́кую}}, {{t+|uk|спаси́бі}}\n* Unami: {{t|unm|wanìshi}}\n* Urdu: {{t+|ur|شُکْرِیَہ}}, {{t|ur|نَوَازِش}},  {{t|ur|مِہَرْبانی|tr=meharbānī}}, {{t|ur|دھنیہ واد|tr=dhanya-vād}} ''(rarely by Hindus)''\n* Uyghur: {{t|ug|رەھمەت}}\n* Uzbek: {{t+|uz|rahmat}}, {{t+|uz|tashakkur}}\n* Vietnamese: {{t+|vi|cám ơn}} ({{t|vi|感恩}}) (''plus one of:'' [[ông]], [[bà#Vietnamese|bà]], [[cô#Vietnamese|cô]], [[anh#Vietnamese|anh]], [[chị]], [[em#Vietnamese|em]], [[quí vị]] &ndash; ''depending on subject of gratitude'')\n* Welsh: {{t+|cy|diolch}}\n* Yiddish: {{t|yi|דאַנק}}\n* Yucatec Maya: {{t|yua|níib óol}}\n* Yup'ik: {{t|esu|quyana}}\n* Zulu: {{t+|zu|ngiyabonga}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{checktrans-top}}\n* Albanian: {{qualifier|2}} {{t+check|sq|faleminderit}}\n* Estonian: {{t+check|et|aitäh}}, {{t-check|et|tänan}}\n* Romanian: {{t-check|ro|mulțumiri|f-p}}, {{qualifier|2}}\n* Woiwurrung: {{t-check|wyi|ngoon godjin}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{en-noun|p|sg=thank<l:obsolete>}}\n\n# {{senseid|en|expression of gratitude}} An [[expression]] of [[appreciation]] or [[gratitude]].\n#: {{ux|en|After all I’ve done, a simple acknowledgment is the '''thanks''' I get?}}\n# [[grateful|Grateful]] [[feeling#Noun|feelings]] or [[thought#Noun|thoughts]]; [[favor#Noun|favour]], [[goodwill]], [[graciousness]].\n\n===Noun===\n{{head|en|noun form}}\n\n# {{lb|en|obsolete}} {{plural of|en|thank}}\n\n====Derived terms====\n{{col|en|thanks to}}\n\n====Translations====\n{{trans-top|expression of gratitude}}\n* American Sign Language: {{t|ase|OpenB@Chin-PalmBack OpenB@FromChin-PalmUp}}\n* Bengali: {{t+|bn|ধন্যবাদ}}, {{t+|bn|শুকরিয়া}}\n* Bulgarian: {{t+|bg|призна́телност|m}}, {{t+|bg|благода́рност}}\n* Catalan: {{t+|ca|mercè|f}}, {{t+|ca|mercès|f}}, {{t+|ca|gràcies|f-p}}\n* Chinese:\n*: Hokkien: {{t+|nan-hbl|多謝|tr=to-siā / to-siǎ / to͘-siā}}\n* Czech: {{t+|cs|díky|m-p}}\n* Danish: {{t+|da|tak|c}}\n* Dutch: {{t+|nl|bedankt}}\n* Esperanto: {{t|eo|danko}}\n* Ewe: {{t|ee|akpe|n}}\n* Faroese: {{t|fo|tøkk}}, {{t|fo|takk}}\n* Finnish: {{t+|fi|kiitos}}, {{t|fi|kiitokset}}\n* French: [[remerciement]]s {{g|m-p}}\n* Galician: {{t|gl|grazas|f-p}}\n* German: {{t+|de|Dank|m}}, {{t|de|Danksagung|f}}\n* Gothic: {{t|got|𐌸𐌰𐌲𐌺𐍃|m}}\n* Greek: {{t+|el|ευχαριστώ|n}}\n* Hebrew: {{t+|he|תּוֹדָה|tr=todá}}\n* Hungarian: {{t+|hu|köszönet}}\n* Hunsrik: {{t|hrx|Dank|m}}\n* Icelandic: {{t+|is|þökk|f}}, {{t|is|þakkargerð|f}}, {{t|is|þakkargjörð|f}}\n* Japanese: {{t+|ja|謝辞|tr=shaji}}\n* Oromo: {{t|om|galata}}\n* Plautdietsch: {{t|pdt|Dank|m}}\n* Polish: {{t+|pl|podzięka|f}}, {{t+|pl|podziękowanie|n}}\n* Portuguese: [[agradecimento]]s {{g|m-p}}\n* Romanian: {{t|ro|mulțumiri|f-p}}\n* Russian: {{t+|ru|благода́рность|f}}\n* Scottish Gaelic: {{t|gd|taing|f}}\n* Sidamo: {{t|sid|galata}}\n* Spanish: {{t+|es|gracias|f-p}}\n* Swedish: {{t+|sv|tack|n}}\n* Tagalog: {{t+|tl|salamat}}, {{t|tl|pagsasalamat}}\n* Tamil: {{t+|ta|நன்றி}}\n* Ukrainian: {{t|uk|подя́ка|f}}\n* Volapük: {{t+|vo|dan}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-top|grateful feelings}}\n* American Sign Language: {{t|ase|OpenB@Chin-PalmBack OpenB@FromChin-PalmUp}}\n* Bulgarian: {{t+|bg|призна́телност|m}}, {{t+|bg|благода́рност}}\n* Dutch: {{t+|nl|dank|m}}\n* Finnish: {{t|fi|kiitokset|p}}\n* French: {{t+|fr|remerciement|m}}\n* German: {{t+|de|Dank|m}}\n* Greek: {{t+|el|ευχαριστία|f}}, {{t+|el|ευγνωμοσύνη|f}}\n*: Ancient Greek: {{t|grc|εὐχαρστία|f}}\n* Hungarian: {{t+|hu|hála}}\n* Italian: {{t+|it|ringraziamento}}\n* Portuguese: {{t+|pt|gratidão|f}}, {{t+|pt|agradecimento}}\n* Russian: {{t+|ru|благода́рность|f}}\n* Spanish: {{t+|es|agradecimiento}}\n* Swedish: {{t+|sv|tack|n}}\n* Tamil: {{t|ta|நன்றிகள்}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{checktrans-top}}\n* Slovak: {{t-check|sk|vďaka}}\n* Tagalog: {{t+check|tl|salamat}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n===Verb===\n{{head|en|verb form}}\n\n# {{infl of|en|thank||s-verb-form}}\n\n{{cln|en|expressions of gratitude}}\n\n==Dutch==\n\n===Etymology===\nBorrowed from {{bor|nl|en|thanks}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|nl|/ˈtɛŋks/}}\n\n===Interjection===\n{{head|nl|interjection}}\n\n# {{lb|nl|informal}} {{l|en|thanks}}\n#: {{syn|nl|bedankt|dank je|dank u|dank je wel|dank u wel|merci}}\n#: {{ux|nl|'''Thanks''' dat je de vaat gisterenavond gedaan had, ik had er zelf geen tijd voor.|'''Thanks''' for doing the dishes yesterday evening, I didn't have time for it myself.}}\n\n{{cln|nl|expressions of gratitude}}"}}